title: fix: make use of allo-allo more secure
body:
With the new usage model there is no checkout or install actions run during the execution of AlloAllo.
I believe this makes it safe enough for use with `pull_request_target`.

I base the above on this information:

> As you can see, the usage of two workflows and passing around workflow artifacts introduces some overhead. If your workflow scenario simply requires commenting on the PR, but does not require a check out of the modified code, using pull_request_target is a logical shortcut.
>
> Unfortunately some repository workflows take this a step further and use pull_request_target with an explicit PR checkout

from: https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-preventing-pwn-requests/
